subSubSection.paragraph:
The name honours Richard L. Hoffman (
1927–2012
) global grand-master of diplopodology through much of the last half of the previous, as well as the first decade of the present century. Vilici is the genitive case of the Latin noun vilicus, meaning ‘steward’, which is also the original meaning of the name Hoffman.

GONOPOD TELOPODITE (
Figs 8B
, 
24
). Solenomere (
slm
) with a long, straight proximal spine (
ps
). Telomere distally with two relatively small branches, folded around each other somewhat like a pair of onefingered hands, the ‘finger’ of the anterior lamella (
al
) having smooth edges, that of the slenderer posterior lamella (
pl
) having jagged edges.
